HEADWORD: Jacchus
<hw>Jac"chus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>Jacchus</ets> a mystic name of Bacchus, Gr. <?/.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The common marmoset (<spn>Hapale
vulgaris</spn>). Formerly, the name was also applied to other species of
the same genus.</def>⟦br⟧
